/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","role":"symbol","title":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Allows to select the balance between result accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK/documentation/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK/SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode39Configuration":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode39Configuration","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode39Configuration","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode39Configuration","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotBarcodeScannerSDK\/SBSDKBarcodeFormatCode39Configuration","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotbarcodescannersdk\/sbsdkbarcodeformatcode39configuration","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Code 39 barcode and derivatives configuration. Add to scanner configuration to scan Code 39, Code 32 (Italian Pharmacode), PZN7 and PZN8 (Pharmazentralnummer) 